<XMLDocContent PageName="cobalt.graphics.IGraphicsDevice.IsTextureFormatSupported" Title="IsTextureFormatSupported method" xmlns="http://www.cobaltrenderer.com/schema/XMLDocSchema.xsd">
  <Paragraph>
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.Welcome">Home</PageRef> ->
    <PageRef PageName="cobalt.graphics.IGraphicsDevice">IGraphicsDevice</PageRef> ->
    IsTextureFormatSupported
  </Paragraph>
  <Section Title="Description">
    <Paragraph>
      The <TypeRef>IsTextureFormatSupported</TypeRef> method returns true if the specified image and data format combination is supported for texture allocation.
    </Paragraph>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="Usage">
    <Code Language="C++"><![CDATA[bool IsTextureFormatSupported(ITextureBuffer::ImageFormat imageFormat, ITextureBuffer::DataFormat dataFormat) const;]]></Code>
    <SubSection Title="Argument list">
      <ArgumentList>
        <ArgumentListEntry Type="ITextureBuffer::ImageFormat" Name="imageFormat">
          The texture image format to test.
        </ArgumentListEntry>
        <ArgumentListEntry Type="ITextureBuffer::DataFormat" Name="dataFormat">
          The texture data format to test in combination with the image format.
        </ArgumentListEntry>
      </ArgumentList>
    </SubSection>
    <SubSection Title="Return value">
      <ReturnValue Type="bool">
        True if the device supports the specified texture format combination, false otherwise.
      </ReturnValue>
    </SubSection>
  </Section>
  <Section Title="See also">
    <PageRefList>
      <PageRefListEntry PageName="cobalt.graphics.IGraphicsDevice">IGraphicsDevice</PageRefListEntry>
    </PageRefList>
  </Section>
</XMLDocContent>
